Twenty people have been killed and 68 others injured in a head-on collision between a tour bus and a cash-in-transit van in Louis Trichardt, Limpopo. The crash took place on the N1 highway last night. According to ER24, the bus then rolled from the freeway bridge into the river below and landed on its left side. ER24 also says most of the people who died down by the river had been trapped under the bus. There have been heavy rains in the area. While details of the crash are still sketchy, police are currently on the scene of the crash. 